Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing after revocation, his probation having been revoked effective 07-19-17.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison system for a total of fifty-four (54) months.   Thirty (30) months initial confinement, followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseing as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is entitled to 404 days sentence credit.   
Minutes.

The State moves to delete the enhancer of within 1000 feet of a school on count 3.  Court grants motion.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of PTC deliver Oxycodone in count 3.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 11-04-14 by 6:00 p.m.;
2) Pay court costs including repayment of the $295.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Maintain fulltime employment, work search or combination;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) No association with any know drug users or dealers;
9) No possession of any prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
The parties stipulate to 44 days credit if revoked.  
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Minutes.
